ial)\n- understands complicated technology (initial)\n- puts concern for others above everything (Agent2)\n- excellent attention skills (Agent2)\n- known to be 100% reliable (Agent1)\n- creates a positive atmosphere with his crew (Agent1)\n\nCandidate D:\n- responds to unexpected events adequately\n- can concentrate very well\n- solves problems extremely well\n- takes responsibility seriously\n- considered moody (initial)\n- regarded as a loner (initial)\n- regarded as a know-it-all (initial)\n- has a hot temper (initial)\n- regarded as arrogant (Agent1)\n- has relatively weak leadership skills (Agent1)\n\nNow evaluate criteria:\n\nReliability: A anticipates dangerous situations (maybe reliability), but no explicit reliability. B conscientious (reliability). C 100% reliable (strong). D takes responsibility seriously (reliability).\n\nTechnical competence: A spatial vision, complex connections (good). B weather assessment, computer skills (good). C understands complicated technology, attention skills (good). D concentration, problem solving (good).\n\nCalmness under pressure: B handles stress well. C keeps calm in crisis. D responds to unexpected events adequately. A not explicit.\n\nCooperation: A leadership but unfriendly, not open to new ideas, not good at criticism, unorganized. B pretentious, wrong tone, nasty remarks, grumpy, uncooperative. C puts concern for others, positive atmosphere, but difficulty communicating, egocentric, low willingness to learn. D moody, loner, arrogant, weak leadership, hot temper.\n\nResponsibility: A leadership, but maybe less. B conscientious. C reliability, concern for others. D takes responsibility seriously.\n\nWe need balanced. Cooperation is critical. Which candidate has least severe cooperation negatives? C has positive atmosphere and concern for others, but communication difficulty and egocentric. A is unfriendly and not open to ideas, criticism issues. B has many negative interpersonal traits (pretentious, nasty remarks). D